race.comment: SKIPPERS CANYON (1) was first up off a break here over 1700m and pulled out an enormous run to win, settling last and having plenty to do in the straight before picking up powerfully to win by a neck. He'll get over even further than this but should be fitter for that and might just be too good again for SIGIRIYA ROCK (10) who looked the winner before being run down late. SIGIRIYA ROCK meets SKIPPERS CANYON better at the weights but does draw wide again. If they push forward and look to slot in he can turn the tables. ENTRUSTING (7) appreciated rising to 1600m last start at Bendigo with a smart win off a good tempo. He's always promised a bit and might be able to go on with it to 1800m. FULL HAO (15) tried hard after covering ground at Flemington last time behind a smart winner. With even luck from the inside she'll go close. ENCHANTED JENNI (12) is flying, this is harder but she's otherwise tough to knock.
